Sentence: I want to visit Paris next summer.
I : pronoun, first person singular, subject of the verb "want"
want : verb "want", first person singular, present tense, active voice
to : particle introducing the infinitive
visit : verb "visit", infinitive form, complement of the verb "want"
Paris : proper noun, city name, direct object of the infinitive "visit"
next : adjective, temporal, modifies "summer"
summer : noun, common, singular, temporal adverbial

Sentence: She enjoys reading mystery novels on weekends.
She : pronoun, third person singular, feminine, subject of the verb "enjoys"
enjoys : verb "enjoy", third person singular, present tense, active voice
reading : verb "read", gerund form, direct object of the verb "enjoys"
mystery : noun, common, singular, acts as adjective modifying "novels"
novels : noun, common, plural, direct object of the gerund "reading"
on : preposition, introduces time phrase
weekends : noun, common, plural, object of the preposition "on"

Sentence: They stopped to buy groceries at the market.
They : pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb "stopped"
stopped : verb "stop", past tense, active voice
to : particle introducing the infinitive
buy : verb "buy", infinitive form, adverbial of purpose modifying "stopped"
groceries : noun, common, plural, direct object of the infinitive "buy"
at : preposition, introduces location
the : definite article, modifies "market"
market : noun, common, singular, object of the preposition "at"

Sentence: He stopped smoking cigarettes last year.
He : pronoun, third person singular, masculine, subject of the verb "stopped"
stopped : verb "stop", past tense, active voice
smoking : verb "smoke", gerund form, direct object of the verb "stopped"
cigarettes : noun, common, plural, direct object of the gerund "smoking"
last : adjective, temporal, modifies "year"
year : noun, common, singular, temporal adverbial

Sentence: We plan to launch the project in April.
We : pronoun, first person plural, subject of the verb "plan"
plan : verb "plan", first person plural, present tense, active voice
to : particle introducing the infinitive
launch : verb "launch", infinitive form, complement of the verb "plan"
the : definite article, modifies "project"
project : noun, common, singular, direct object of the infinitive "launch"
in : preposition, introduces time phrase
April : proper noun, month name, object of the preposition "in"

Sentence: Maria avoids driving during heavy rain.
Maria : proper noun, person name, subject of the verb "avoids"
avoids : verb "avoid", third person singular, present tense, active voice
driving : verb "drive", gerund form, direct object of the verb "avoids"
during : preposition, introduces time condition
heavy : adjective, modifies "rain"
rain : noun, common, singular, object of the preposition "during"

Sentence: The team decided to extend the deadline.
The : definite article, modifies "team"
team : noun, common, singular, subject of the verb "decided"
decided : verb "decide", past tense, active voice
to : particle introducing the infinitive
extend : verb "extend", infinitive form, complement of the verb "decided"
the : definite article, modifies "deadline"
deadline : noun, common, singular, direct object of the infinitive "extend"

Sentence: Children love playing soccer in the park.
Children : noun, common, plural, subject of the verb "love"
love : verb "love", present tense, active voice
playing : verb "play", gerund form, direct object of the verb "love"
soccer : noun, common, singular, direct object of the gerund "playing"
in : preposition, introduces location
the : definite article, modifies "park"
park : noun, common, singular, object of the preposition "in"

Sentence: She paused to answer the phone call.
She : pronoun, third person singular, feminine, subject of the verb "paused"
paused : verb "pause", past tense, active voice
to : particle introducing the infinitive
answer : verb "answer", infinitive form, adverbial of purpose modifying "paused"
the : definite article, modifies "phone"
phone : noun, common, singular, part of compound noun "phone call"
call : noun, common, singular, direct object of the infinitive "answer"

Sentence: I dislike waiting in long lines at the bank.
I : pronoun, first person singular, subject of the verb "dislike"
dislike : verb "dislike", first person singular, present tense, active voice
waiting : verb "wait", gerund form, direct object of the verb "dislike"
in : preposition, introduces location/state
long : adjective, modifies "lines"
lines : noun, common, plural, object of the preposition "in"
at : preposition, introduces location
the : definite article, modifies "bank"
bank : noun, common, singular, object of the preposition "at"

Sentence: The manager agreed to sign the contract today.
The : definite article, modifies "manager"
manager : noun, common, singular, subject of the verb "agreed"
agreed : verb "agree", past tense, active voice
to : particle introducing the infinitive
sign : verb "sign", infinitive form, complement of the verb "agreed"
the : definite article, modifies "contract"
contract : noun, common, singular, direct object of the infinitive "sign"
today : adverb, temporal, modifies the clause

Sentence: He keeps forgetting to lock the front door.
He : pronoun, third person singular, masculine, subject of the verb "keeps"
keeps : verb "keep", third person singular, present tense, active voice
forgetting : verb "forget", gerund form, direct object of the verb "keeps"
to : particle introducing the infinitive
lock : verb "lock", infinitive form, complement of the gerund "forgetting"
the : definite article, modifies "door"
front : adjective, modifies "door"
door : noun, common, singular, direct object of the infinitive "lock"

Sentence: They considered moving to a new city.
They : pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb "considered"
considered : verb "consider", past tense, active voice
moving : verb "move", gerund form, direct object of the verb "considered"
to : preposition, introduces destination
a : indefinite article, modifies "city"
new : adjective, modifies "city"
city : noun, common, singular, object of the preposition "to"

Sentence: My sister hopes to become a doctor soon.
My : possessive adjective, first person singular, modifies "sister"
sister : noun, common, singular, subject of the verb "hopes"
hopes : verb "hope", third person singular, present tense, active voice
to : particle introducing the infinitive
become : verb "become", infinitive form, complement of the verb "hopes"
a : indefinite article, modifies "doctor"
doctor : noun, common, singular, subject complement of the infinitive "become"
soon : adverb, temporal, modifies the clause

Sentence: The dog started barking at the mail carrier.
The : definite article, modifies "dog"
dog : noun, common, singular, subject of the verb "started"
started : verb "start", past tense, active voice
barking : verb "bark", gerund form, direct object of the verb "started"
at : preposition, introduces target
the : definite article, modifies "carrier"
mail : noun, common, singular, acts as adjective modifying "carrier"
carrier : noun, common, singular, object of the preposition "at"
